Kaveel Singh, News24Umhlanga Gateway Mall. (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; A brazen jewellery store robbery saw suspects open fire at the popular Gateway Mall on Wednesday, police said. Lieutenant-Colonel Shooz Magudulela said three men entered the jewellery store at 09:30. &ldquo;They opened fire and took two boxes of jewellery and fled the scene in their grey BMW. The vehicle was later found abandoned at a construction site. It was established that it was hijacked in Berea on June 20, 2016. No injuries were sustained by the employees.&rdquo;Magudulela said no were arrests made, but police were still searching for the suspects. Magudulela added that police &ldquo;did not know where the getaway vehicle was parked at this stage&rdquo;.He did not reveal the name of the jewellery store.&nbsp;A case of business robbery has been opened at Durban North police station for investigation.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.